value.value: 全身の創傷
injuries resulting in damage that tears or breaks tissue occurring across the whole body
全身の開放性擦過傷
damage to the skin consisting of loss of the epidermis and portions of the dermis but not the complete thickness of the skin, occurring across the whole body
全身の開放性剥離
a wound or wounds where the tissue has been torn from its attachment, occurring across the whole body; avulsion of skin on the extremities is sometimes called degloving
全身の開放性切開
a wound or wounds created by a sharp object, occurring across the whole body; edges are smooth and trauma to surrounding tissue is minimal
全身の開放性裂傷
an irregular wound or wounds created by tearing of tissue, occurring across the whole body; damage to both superficial and underlying tissue is variable
全身の開放性刺傷
a penetrating wound or wounds occurring across the whole body caused by pointed object (e.g. bite)
全身の閉鎖性挫傷
damage of the skin and/or underlying strutures occurring across the whole body without breaking the skin (e.g. bruising, crush)
